    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A Garou can assume multiple sacred forms, each representing a balance between human, wolf, and spirit</p><p>These forms alter how the Garou interacts with the world, affecting combat presence, social impact, movement, and spiritual resonance.</p><p>The Garou’s forms include:</p><p>• Homid – Human form</p><p>• Glabro – Near-human war form</p><p>• Crinos – War form of legend</p><p>• Hispo – Dire wolf form</p><p>• Lupus – Natural wolf form</p><p>Each form has unique strengths, limitations, and interactions with Rage, Gnosis, and Delirium. The effects of each form are defined by additional Garou features.</p><p></p><p>Rules:</p><ul data-start=\"362\" data-end=\"523\"><li data-start=\"362\" data-end=\"385\"><p data-start=\"364\" data-end=\"385\">What shapeshifting is</p></li><li data-start=\"386\" data-end=\"430\"><p data-start=\"388\" data-end=\"430\">Action economy (bonus action, free revert)</p></li><li data-start=\"431\" data-end=\"450\"><p data-start=\"433\" data-end=\"450\">Rage requirements</p></li><li data-start=\"451\" data-end=\"470\"><p data-start=\"453\" data-end=\"470\">Equipment melding</p></li><li data-start=\"471\" data-end=\"497\"><p data-start=\"473\" data-end=\"497\">Reversion when Rage ends</p></li><li data-start=\"498\" data-end=\"523\"><p data-start=\"500\" data-end=\"523\">Any general limitations</p></li></ul><p></p>",
